# System Design

## Modularity
- Each pipeline stage (STT, TTS, VAD, LLM, context) behind an abstract interface
- One responsibility per module; avoid god objects
- Depend on abstractions, not concrete implementations

## Interfaces
- Define ABCs in `*/base.py` with clear contracts
- Use factory functions (`create_*_engine()`) for construction
- New engines: implement interface → add factory branch → add config → add tests

## Boundaries
- External APIs (Anthropic, OpenAI, ElevenLabs) behind interfaces; mock in tests
- Config via pydantic-settings; no hardcoded secrets or env-specific logic
- Fail at boundaries: validate inputs, handle errors, fallback gracefully

## Data Flow
- Prefer streaming over batch where latency matters (LLM → TTS)
- Keep pipeline stages loosely coupled; pass data, not callbacks
- Avoid shared mutable state; use explicit parameters and return values
